messages: dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:42): so what kind of music are you into?
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:43): The clarinet and bass clarinet..
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:44): I used to play that
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:44): except you don't now.. so not cool :p
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:45): well I'm a woodwind at heart
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:45): I am brass through and through
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:46): haha.. at least you dont play strings... :P
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:47): So did you or do you march?
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:49): still do.. but not like you do in the US... mostly street marches
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:49): yeah.. I know.. but we dont do formations or anything cool
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:50): So military style? Or just plain old forward marching?
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:51): plain old forward marching... british brass band style
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:52): and only because we have to... rather lame actually :(
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:52): but the music is good... on stage and competition
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:53): I hate concert season. Love marching season though
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:54): It is a completely different culture over there music wise.. really interesting
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:54): I never eally looked into it
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:55): I guess you wouldnt when you are part of it
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:55): Yes. Basically, I can't focus on anything else with how hard they work us
dba98cfe31dd2c675f5bac7ade246499 (11:57): it is kind of dying a little in Australia.. everything else is more important.. soccer and cricket
d8b791549a3cac71b59b9d3152661744 (11:58): Well I have to go. Nice talking
